46const char *program = "dnssec-settime";
47int verbose;
48
49static isc_mem_t *mctx = NULL;
50
51ISC_PLATFORM_NORETURN_PRE static void
52usage(void) ISC_PLATFORM_NORETURN_POST;
53
54static void
55usage(void) {
56 fprintf(stderr, "Usage:\n");
57 fprintf(stderr, " %s [options] keyfile\n\n", program);
58 fprintf(stderr, "Version: %s\n", VERSION);
59 fprintf(stderr, "General options:\n");
60#if USE_PKCS11
61 fprintf(stderr, " -E engine: specify PKCS#11 provider "
62 "(default: %s)\n", PK11_LIB_LOCATION);
63#elif defined(USE_PKCS11)
64 fprintf(stderr, " -E engine: specify OpenSSL engine "
65 "(default \"pkcs11\")\n");
66#else
67 fprintf(stderr, " -E engine: specify OpenSSL engine\n");
68#endif
69 fprintf(stderr, " -f: force update of old-style "
70 "keys\n");
71 fprintf(stderr, " -K directory: set key file location\n");
72 fprintf(stderr, " -L ttl: set default key TTL\n");
73 fprintf(stderr, " -v level: set level of verbosity\n");
74 fprintf(stderr, " -V: print version information\n");
75 fprintf(stderr, " -h: help\n");
76 fprintf(stderr, "Timing options:\n");
77 fprintf(stderr, " -P date/[+-]offset/none: set/unset key "
78 "publication date\n");
79 fprintf(stderr, " -P sync date/[+-]offset/none: set/unset "
80 "CDS and CDNSKEY publication date\n");
81 fprintf(stderr, " -A date/[+-]offset/none: set/unset key "
82 "activation date\n");
83 fprintf(stderr, " -R date/[+-]offset/none: set/unset key "
84 "revocation date\n");
85 fprintf(stderr, " -I date/[+-]offset/none: set/unset key "
86 "inactivation date\n");
87 fprintf(stderr, " -D date/[+-]offset/none: set/unset key "
88 "deletion date\n");
89 fprintf(stderr, " -D sync date/[+-]offset/none: set/unset "
90 "CDS and CDNSKEY deletion date\n");
91 fprintf(stderr, " -S <key>: generate a successor to an existing "
92 "key\n");
93 fprintf(stderr, " -i <interval>: prepublication interval for "
94 "successor key "
95 "(default: 30 days)\n");
96 fprintf(stderr, "Printing options:\n");
97 fprintf(stderr, " -p C/P/Psync/A/R/I/D/Dsync/all: print a "
98 "particular time value or values\n");
99 fprintf(stderr, " -u: print times in unix epoch "
100 "format\n");
101 fprintf(stderr, "Output:\n");
102 fprintf(stderr, " K<name>+<alg>+<new id>.key, "
103 "K<name>+<alg>+<new id>.private\n");
104
105 exit (-1);
106}
107
108static void
109printtime(dst_key_t *key, int type, const char *tag, bool epoch,
110 FILE *stream)
111{
112 isc_result_t result;
113 const char *output = NULL;
114 isc_stdtime_t when;
115
116 if (tag != NULL)
117 fprintf(stream, "%s: ", tag);
118
119 result = dst_key_gettime(key, type, &when);
120 if (result == ISC_R_NOTFOUND) {
121 fprintf(stream, "UNSET\n");
122 } else if (epoch) {
123 fprintf(stream, "%d\n", (int) when);
124 } else {
125 time_t timet = when;
126 output = ctime(&timet);
127 fprintf(stream, "%s", output);
128 }
129}
130
131int
132main(int argc, char **argv) {
133 isc_result_t result;
134 const char *engine = NULL;
135 const char *filename = NULL;
136 char *directory = NULL;
137 char newname[1024];
138 char keystr[DST_KEY_FORMATSIZE];
139 char *endp, *p;
140 int ch;
141 const char *predecessor = NULL;
142 dst_key_t *prevkey = NULL;
143 dst_key_t *key = NULL;
144 isc_buffer_t buf;
145 dns_name_t *name = NULL;
146 dns_secalg_t alg = 0;
147 unsigned int size = 0;
148 uint16_t flags = 0;
149 int prepub = -1;
150 dns_ttl_t ttl = 0;
151 isc_stdtime_t now;
152 isc_stdtime_t pub = 0, act = 0, rev = 0, inact = 0, del = 0;
153 isc_stdtime_t prevact = 0, previnact = 0, prevdel = 0;
154 bool setpub = false, setact = false;
155 bool setrev = false, setinact = false;
156 bool setdel = false, setttl = false;
157 bool unsetpub = false, unsetact = false;
158 bool unsetrev = false, unsetinact = false;
159 bool unsetdel = false;
160 bool printcreate = false, printpub = false;
161 bool printact = false, printrev = false;
162 bool printinact = false, printdel = false;
163 bool force = false;
164 bool epoch = false;
165 bool changed = false;
166 isc_log_t *log = NULL;
167 isc_stdtime_t syncadd = 0, syncdel = 0;
168 bool unsetsyncadd = false, setsyncadd = false;
169 bool unsetsyncdel = false, setsyncdel = false;
170 bool printsyncadd = false, printsyncdel = false;
171
172 if (argc == 1)
173 usage();
174
175 result = isc_mem_create(0, 0, &mctx);
176 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
177 fatal("Out of memory");
178
179 setup_logging(mctx, &log);
180
181#if USE_PKCS11
182 pk11_result_register();
183#endif
184 dns_result_register();
185
186 isc_commandline_errprint = false;
187
188 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
189
190#define CMDLINE_FLAGS "A:D:E:fhI:i:K:L:P:p:R:S:uv:V"
191 while ((ch = isc_commandline_parse(argc, argv, CMDLINE_FLAGS)) != -1) {
192 switch (ch) {
193 case 'E':
194 engine = isc_commandline_argument;
195 break;
196 case 'f':
197 force = true;
198 break;
199 case 'p':
200 p = isc_commandline_argument;
201 if (!strcasecmp(p, "all")) {
202 printcreate = true;
203 printpub = true;
204 printact = true;
205 printrev = true;
206 printinact = true;
207 printdel = true;
208 printsyncadd = true;
209 printsyncdel = true;
210 break;
211 }
212
213 do {
214 switch (*p++) {
215 case 'C':
216 printcreate = true;
217 break;
218 case 'P':
219 if (!strncmp(p, "sync", 4)) {
220 p += 4;
221 printsyncadd = true;
222 break;
223 }
224 printpub = true;
225 break;
226 case 'A':
227 printact = true;
228 break;
229 case 'R':
230 printrev = true;
231 break;
232 case 'I':
233 printinact = true;
234 break;
235 case 'D':
236 if (!strncmp(p, "sync", 4)) {
237 p += 4;
238 printsyncdel = true;
239 break;
240 }
241 printdel = true;
242 break;
243 case ' ':
244 break;
245 default:
246 usage();
247 break;
248 }
249 } while (*p != '\0');
250 break;
251 case 'u':
252 epoch = true;
253 break;
254 case 'K':
255 /*
256 * We don't have to copy it here, but do it to
257 * simplify cleanup later
258 */
259 directory = isc_mem_strdup(mctx,
260 isc_commandline_argument);
261 if (directory == NULL) {
262 fatal("Failed to allocate memory for "
263 "directory");
264 }
265 break;
266 case 'L':
267 ttl = strtottl(isc_commandline_argument);
268 setttl = true;
269 break;
270 case 'v':
271 verbose = strtol(isc_commandline_argument, &endp, 0);
272 if (*endp != '\0')
273 fatal("-v must be followed by a number");
274 break;
275 case 'P':
276 /* -Psync ? */
277 if (isoptarg("sync", argv, usage)) {
278 if (unsetsyncadd || setsyncadd)
279 fatal("-P sync specified more than "
280 "once");
281
282 changed = true;
283 syncadd = strtotime(isc_commandline_argument,
284 now, now, &setsyncadd);
285 unsetsyncadd = !setsyncadd;
286 break;
287 }
288 (void)isoptarg("dnskey", argv, usage);
289 if (setpub || unsetpub)
290 fatal("-P specified more than once");
291
292 changed = true;
293 pub = strtotime(isc_commandline_argument,
294 now, now, &setpub);
295 unsetpub = !setpub;
296 break;
297 case 'A':
298 if (setact || unsetact)
299 fatal("-A specified more than once");
300
301 changed = true;
302 act = strtotime(isc_commandline_argument,
303 now, now, &setact);
304 unsetact = !setact;
305 break;
306 case 'R':
307 if (setrev || unsetrev)
308 fatal("-R specified more than once");
309
310 changed = true;
311 rev = strtotime(isc_commandline_argument,
312 now, now, &setrev);
313 unsetrev = !setrev;
314 break;
315 case 'I':
316 if (setinact || unsetinact)
317 fatal("-I specified more than once");
318
319 changed = true;
320 inact = strtotime(isc_commandline_argument,
321 now, now, &setinact);
322 unsetinact = !setinact;
323 break;
324 case 'D':
325 /* -Dsync ? */
326 if (isoptarg("sync", argv, usage)) {
327 if (unsetsyncdel || setsyncdel)
328 fatal("-D sync specified more than "
329 "once");
330
331 changed = true;
332 syncdel = strtotime(isc_commandline_argument,
333 now, now, &setsyncdel);
334 unsetsyncdel = !setsyncdel;
335 break;
336 }
337 /* -Ddnskey ? */
338 (void)isoptarg("dnskey", argv, usage);
339 if (setdel || unsetdel)
340 fatal("-D specified more than once");
341
342 changed = true;
343 del = strtotime(isc_commandline_argument,
344 now, now, &setdel);
345 unsetdel = !setdel;
346 break;
347 case 'S':
348 predecessor = isc_commandline_argument;
349 break;
350 case 'i':
351 prepub = strtottl(isc_commandline_argument);
352 break;
353 case '?':
354 if (isc_commandline_option != '?')
355 fprintf(stderr, "%s: invalid argument -%c\n",
356 program, isc_commandline_option);
357 /* FALLTHROUGH */
358 case 'h':
359 /* Does not return. */
360 usage();
361
362 case 'V':
363 /* Does not return. */
364 version(program);
365
366 default:
367 fprintf(stderr, "%s: unhandled option -%c\n",
368 program, isc_commandline_option);
369 exit(1);
370 }
371 }
372
373 if (argc < isc_commandline_index + 1 ||
374 argv[isc_commandline_index] == NULL)
375 fatal("The key file name was not specified");
376 if (argc > isc_commandline_index + 1)
377 fatal("Extraneous arguments");
378
379 result = dst_lib_init(mctx, engine);
380 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
381 fatal("Could not initialize dst: %s",
382 isc_result_totext(result));
383
384 if (predecessor != NULL) {
385 int major, minor;
386
387 if (prepub == -1)
388 prepub = (30 * 86400);
389
390 if (setpub || unsetpub)
391 fatal("-S and -P cannot be used together");
392 if (setact || unsetact)
393 fatal("-S and -A cannot be used together");
394
395 result = dst_key_fromnamedfile(predecessor, directory,
396 DST_TYPE_PUBLIC |
397 DST_TYPE_PRIVATE,
398 mctx, &prevkey);
399 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
400 fatal("Invalid keyfile %s: %s",
401 filename, isc_result_totext(result));
402 if (!dst_key_isprivate(prevkey) && !dst_key_isexternal(prevkey))
403 fatal("%s is not a private key", filename);
404
405 name = dst_key_name(prevkey);
406 alg = dst_key_alg(prevkey);
407 size = dst_key_size(prevkey);
408 flags = dst_key_flags(prevkey);
409
410 dst_key_format(prevkey, keystr, sizeof(keystr));
411 dst_key_getprivateformat(prevkey, &major, &minor);
412 if (major != DST_MAJOR_VERSION || minor < DST_MINOR_VERSION)
413 fatal("Predecessor has incompatible format "
414 "version %d.%d\n\t", major, minor);
415
416 result = dst_key_gettime(prevkey, DST_TIME_ACTIVATE, &prevact);
417 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
418 fatal("Predecessor has no activation date. "
419 "You must set one before\n\t"
420 "generating a successor.");
421
422 result = dst_key_gettime(prevkey, DST_TIME_INACTIVE,
423 &previnact);
424 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
425 fatal("Predecessor has no inactivation date. "
426 "You must set one before\n\t"
427 "generating a successor.");
428
429 pub = previnact - prepub;
430 act = previnact;
431
432 if ((previnact - prepub) < now && prepub != 0)
433 fatal("Time until predecessor inactivation is\n\t"
434 "shorter than the prepublication interval. "
435 "Either change\n\t"
436 "predecessor inactivation date, or use the -i "
437 "option to set\n\t"
438 "a shorter prepublication interval.");
439
440 result = dst_key_gettime(prevkey, DST_TIME_DELETE, &prevdel);
441 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
442 fprintf(stderr, "%s: warning: Predecessor has no "
443 "removal date;\n\t"
444 "it will remain in the zone "
445 "indefinitely after rollover.\n",
446 program);
447 else if (prevdel < previnact)
448 fprintf(stderr, "%s: warning: Predecessor is "
449 "scheduled to be deleted\n\t"
450 "before it is scheduled to be "
451 "inactive.\n", program);
452
453 changed = setpub = setact = true;
454 } else {
455 if (prepub < 0)
456 prepub = 0;
457
458 if (prepub > 0) {
459 if (setpub && setact && (act - prepub) < pub)
460 fatal("Activation and publication dates "
461 "are closer together than the\n\t"
462 "prepublication interval.");
463
464 if (setpub && !setact) {
465 setact = true;
466 act = pub + prepub;
467 } else if (setact && !setpub) {
468 setpub = true;
469 pub = act - prepub;
470 }
471
472 if ((act - prepub) < now)
473 fatal("Time until activation is shorter "
474 "than the\n\tprepublication interval.");
475 }
476 }
477
478 if (directory != NULL) {
479 filename = argv[isc_commandline_index];
480 } else {
481 result = isc_file_splitpath(mctx, argv[isc_commandline_index],
482 &directory, &filename);
483 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
484 fatal("cannot process filename %s: %s",
485 argv[isc_commandline_index],
486 isc_result_totext(result));
487 }
488
489 result = dst_key_fromnamedfile(filename, directory,
490 DST_TYPE_PUBLIC | DST_TYPE_PRIVATE,
491 mctx, &key);
492 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
493 fatal("Invalid keyfile %s: %s",
494 filename, isc_result_totext(result));
495
496 if (!dst_key_isprivate(key) && !dst_key_isexternal(key))
497 fatal("%s is not a private key", filename);
498
499 dst_key_format(key, keystr, sizeof(keystr));
500
501 if (predecessor != NULL) {
502 if (!dns_name_equal(name, dst_key_name(key)))
503 fatal("Key name mismatch");
504 if (alg != dst_key_alg(key))
505 fatal("Key algorithm mismatch");
506 if (size != dst_key_size(key))
507 fatal("Key size mismatch");
508 if (flags != dst_key_flags(key))
509 fatal("Key flags mismatch");
510 }
511
512 prevdel = previnact = 0;
513 if ((setdel && setinact && del < inact) ||
514 (dst_key_gettime(key, DST_TIME_INACTIVE,
515 &previnact) == ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
516 setdel && !setinact && !unsetinact && del < previnact) ||
517 (dst_key_gettime(key, DST_TIME_DELETE,
518 &prevdel) == ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
519 setinact && !setdel && !unsetdel && prevdel < inact) ||
520 (!setdel && !unsetdel && !setinact && !unsetinact &&
521 prevdel != 0 && prevdel < previnact))
522 fprintf(stderr, "%s: warning: Key is scheduled to "
523 "be deleted before it is\n\t"
524 "scheduled to be inactive.\n",
525 program);
526
527 if (force)
528 set_keyversion(key);
529 else
530 check_keyversion(key, keystr);
531
532 if (verbose > 2)
533 fprintf(stderr, "%s: %s\n", program, keystr);
534
535 /*
536 * Set time values.
537 */
538 if (setpub)
539 dst_key_settime(key, DST_TIME_PUBLISH, pub);
540 else if (unsetpub)
541 dst_key_unsettime(key, DST_TIME_PUBLISH);
542
543 if (setact)
544 dst_key_settime(key, DST_TIME_ACTIVATE, act);
545 else if (unsetact)
546 dst_key_unsettime(key, DST_TIME_ACTIVATE);
547
548 if (setrev) {
549 if ((dst_key_flags(key) & DNS_KEYFLAG_REVOKE) != 0)
550 fprintf(stderr, "%s: warning: Key %s is already "
551 "revoked; changing the revocation date "
552 "will not affect this.\n",
553 program, keystr);
554 if ((dst_key_flags(key) & DNS_KEYFLAG_KSK) == 0)
555 fprintf(stderr, "%s: warning: Key %s is not flagged as "
556 "a KSK, but -R was used. Revoking a "
557 "ZSK is legal, but undefined.\n",
558 program, keystr);
559 dst_key_settime(key, DST_TIME_REVOKE, rev);
560 } else if (unsetrev) {
561 if ((dst_key_flags(key) & DNS_KEYFLAG_REVOKE) != 0)
562 fprintf(stderr, "%s: warning: Key %s is already "
563 "revoked; removing the revocation date "
564 "will not affect this.\n",
565 program, keystr);
566 dst_key_unsettime(key, DST_TIME_REVOKE);
567 }
568
569 if (setinact)
570 dst_key_settime(key, DST_TIME_INACTIVE, inact);
571 else if (unsetinact)
572 dst_key_unsettime(key, DST_TIME_INACTIVE);
573
574 if (setdel)
575 dst_key_settime(key, DST_TIME_DELETE, del);
576 else if (unsetdel)
577 dst_key_unsettime(key, DST_TIME_DELETE);
578
579 if (setsyncadd)
580 dst_key_settime(key, DST_TIME_SYNCPUBLISH, syncadd);
581 else if (unsetsyncadd)
582 dst_key_unsettime(key, DST_TIME_SYNCPUBLISH);
583
584 if (setsyncdel)
585 dst_key_settime(key, DST_TIME_SYNCDELETE, syncdel);
586 else if (unsetsyncdel)
587 dst_key_unsettime(key, DST_TIME_SYNCDELETE);
588
589 if (setttl)
590 dst_key_setttl(key, ttl);
591
592 /*
593 * No metadata changes were made but we're forcing an upgrade
594 * to the new format anyway: use "-P now -A now" as the default
595 */
596 if (force && !changed) {
597 dst_key_settime(key, DST_TIME_PUBLISH, now);
598 dst_key_settime(key, DST_TIME_ACTIVATE, now);
599 changed = true;
600 }
601
602 if (!changed && setttl)
603 changed = true;
604
605 /*
606 * Print out time values, if -p was used.
607 */
608 if (printcreate)
609 printtime(key, DST_TIME_CREATED, "Created", epoch, stdout);
610
611 if (printpub)
612 printtime(key, DST_TIME_PUBLISH, "Publish", epoch, stdout);
613
614 if (printact)
615 printtime(key, DST_TIME_ACTIVATE, "Activate", epoch, stdout);
616
617 if (printrev)
618 printtime(key, DST_TIME_REVOKE, "Revoke", epoch, stdout);
619
620 if (printinact)
621 printtime(key, DST_TIME_INACTIVE, "Inactive", epoch, stdout);
622
623 if (printdel)
624 printtime(key, DST_TIME_DELETE, "Delete", epoch, stdout);
625
626 if (printsyncadd)
627 printtime(key, DST_TIME_SYNCPUBLISH, "SYNC Publish",
628 epoch, stdout);
629
630 if (printsyncdel)
631 printtime(key, DST_TIME_SYNCDELETE, "SYNC Delete",
632 epoch, stdout);
633
634 if (changed) {
635 isc_buffer_init(&buf, newname, sizeof(newname));
636 result = dst_key_buildfilename(key, DST_TYPE_PUBLIC, directory,
637 &buf);
638 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
639 fatal("Failed to build public key filename: %s",
640 isc_result_totext(result));
641 }
642
643 result = dst_key_tofile(key, DST_TYPE_PUBLIC|DST_TYPE_PRIVATE,
644 directory);
645 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
646 dst_key_format(key, keystr, sizeof(keystr));
647 fatal("Failed to write key %s: %s", keystr,
648 isc_result_totext(result));
649 }
650
651 printf("%s\n", newname);
652
653 isc_buffer_clear(&buf);
654 result = dst_key_buildfilename(key, DST_TYPE_PRIVATE, directory,
655 &buf);
656 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
657 fatal("Failed to build private key filename: %s",
658 isc_result_totext(result));
659 }
660 printf("%s\n", newname);
661 }
662
663 if (prevkey != NULL)
664 dst_key_free(&prevkey);
665 dst_key_free(&key);
666 dst_lib_destroy();
667 if (verbose > 10)
668 isc_mem_stats(mctx, stdout);
669 cleanup_logging(&log);
670 isc_mem_free(mctx, directory);
671 isc_mem_destroy(&mctx);
672
673 return (0);
674}
